Let us now compute the current ratio using its equation:

$$ \begin{aligned}
\text{Current ratio} &= \dfrac{\text{\$6,760}}{\text{\$4,590}}\\[15pt]

&= \boxed{\text{1.47 times}}
\end{aligned}$$

**As can be seen in the computation, its current liabilities can be covered by its current assets of $1.47 to every $1 current liability.**
